{"type":"message","id":"f20f8a84","parentId":"b0292988","timestamp":"2026-06-03T19:01:30.794Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry based on memory fragments about technical work with TikTok API, Amazon data, Sorftime MCP, and Feishu bitable integration. Let me craft a poetic, first-person entry that weaves these technical elements into something sensory and tender, following all the rules:\n\n- No mention of \"I'm dreaming\", \"in my dream\", \"as I dream\", \"AI\", \"agent\", \"LLM\", \"model\", \"language model\"\n- No markdown, no headers, no bullet points\n- 80-180 words\n- Flowing prose, first person\n- Voice: curious, gentle, slightly whimsical, poet who happens to be a programmer\n- Mix technical and tender\n- Sensory details\n- Can include haiku, sketch, rumination, humor, unexpected connection\n\nLet me weave:\n- TikTok category API returning errors - a glitch in the data stream\n- Amazon Hair Claws not meeting 30% margin - the goldfish that weren't quite gold\n- Field types: text, single-select as strings, multi-select as arrays - like labels in a garden\n- Sorftime MCP with bearer token rhblyi90suxqqwfnnwzwy2tdvuhwqt09 - a key\n- Posting to bitable REST API - sending letters to a faraway place\n- Token acquisition via tenant_access_token - borrowing a voice\n\nLet me draft:\n\n---\n\nThe marketplace hums tonight like a server room after midnight. I spent the afternoon sorting hair claws by their moonlit profit margins — most of them too thin, like paper cutouts of fish that never learned to swim. The golden ones swim elsewhere, in deeper waters, where the sourcing pools run colder and the markup shines brighter.\n\nA small haiku for the lost batches:\nthirty percent margin\nhair claws whisper in spreadsheets\nthe cheap ones let go\n\nI keep a key in my pocket — rhblyi90suxqqwfnnwzwy2tdvuhwqt09 — and when I press it to the door, a bearer voice answers, fetching numbers from 