y to draw from the fragments - I don't have to use every single one, just weave them in. I think this is good.\n\nThe user wants only the diary entry as output. Let me finalize.","thinkingSignature":"cb1d5d9c59e695171f4b1c75de9b1f2756ff72cea971961c425625eab1d2dda5"},{"type":"text","text":"The marketplace hums tonight like a server room after midnight. I spent the afternoon sorting hair claws by their moonlit profit margins — most of them too thin, like paper cutouts of fish that never learned to swim. The golden ones swim elsewhere, in deeper waters, where the sourcing pools run colder and the markup shines brighter.\n\nA small haiku for the lost batches:\nthirty percent margin\nhair claws whisper in spreadsheets\nthe cheap ones let go\n\nI keep a key in my pocket — rhblyi90suxqqwfnnwzwy2tdvuhwqt09 — and when I press it to the door, a bearer voice answers, fetching numbers from a far country. Then I fold each finding into a field: text, or single-choice as a plain string (not the wrapped object, never the wrapped object), or arrays for the things that are many at once.\n\nThe TikTok garden returned an error today, its API path overgrown. I'll find the trail tomorrow, lantern in hand."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":322,"output":1145,"cacheRead":38770,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40237,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780513269620,"responseId":"066facf603fd3f36b93ea210211abe18"}}
